{"article_id":"6krjh9HZ8vvPKKvf","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"( CNN )","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"The United States now has the highest number of known cases of coronavirus in the world with more than 82,000 ,","depth":10},{"id":2,"text":"according to CNN 's tally of cases","depth":11},{"id":3,"text":"reported by health officials .","depth":11},{"id":4,"text":"The US cases piled up Thursday ,","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"surpassing China and Italy .","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"The per capita rate of cases varies","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"because of the countries ' vast differences in population .","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"As of Thursday evening , the United States had at least 82,100 cases","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"while China was reporting 81,782 .","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"There have been more than 510,000 cases reported worldwide .","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"The countries ' numbers are changing constantly","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"and both the totals and the rank order of countries could change at any time .","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"The grim milestone comes","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"just as US officials said","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"there was a new high for fatalities","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"reported in a single day .","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"At least 246 new deaths were reported Thursday ,","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"bringing the total number of deaths nationwide to at least 1,195 .","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"The spike of cases has hospitals around the country scrambling to keep up with the demand for care .","depth":5},{"id":20,"text":"In New York ,","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"where more than half of the US cases have been reported ,","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"exhausted hospital workers are turning to increasingly desperate measures","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"to combat the virus .","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"New York Bellevue Hospital Center created a makeshift morgue","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"using tents and refrigerated trucks .","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"At Elmhurst Hospital Center in Queens , 13 patients died from coronavirus within 24 hours","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"A registered nurse described what she has experienced inside a Long Island hospital and the toll","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"that caring for coronavirus patients is taking on health care workers .","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"`` I have n't slept","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"because my mind wo n't shut off .","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"I cried in the bathroom on my break ,","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"as I peeled off the PPE from my sweaty self ,","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"mask indentations on my face .","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"I cried the entire ride home , ''","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"the nurse wrote in a social media post .","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"The nurse ,","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"whom CNN is not naming ,","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"says","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"patients are streaming in with `` non stop coughing , sweaty , fevers '' and with `` fear in their eyes . ''","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"`` I cry for the ones","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"who passed away .","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"I cry","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"because we intubated 5 patients within 10 min","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"and im terrified .","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"I cry for my co workers ,","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"because we know","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"it will get worse","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"and I already feel like","depth":13},{"id":49,"text":"that is impossible","depth":13},{"id":50,"text":"and we are already at our breaking point ,","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"I cry for the parents , children , siblings , spouses","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"who can not be with their loved ones","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"who may be dying","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"but cant have visitors","depth":13},{"id":55,"text":"because there is no visiting allowed , ''","depth":13},{"id":56,"text":"the nurse added .","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"Outbreaks in New York , Washington and California have captured the nation 's attention for weeks","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"--","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"but some health officials predict","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"areas of Michigan and Illinois could be the next epicenters of the crisis .","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"Dr. Deborah Birx , the White House 's coronavirus response coordinator , said","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"health officials are concerned","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"that counties like Wayne County , Michigan and Cook County , Illinois are showing a `` more rapid increase '' in cases .","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"Birx noted","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"that 40 % of the country has `` extraordinary low rates '' of coronavirus ''","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"About 19 states have fewer than 200 cases ,","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"she said .","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"Louisiana ,","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"which has seen coronavirus cases climb this week ,","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"is already emerging as another hot spot .","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"New Orleans is facing critical shortages of ventilators and protective equipment ,","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"an official told CNN Thursday .","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"`` This is going to be the disaster","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"that defines our generation , ''","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"Collin Arnold , director of the city 's Homeland Security and Emergency Preparedness , said .","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"Health officials said","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"they are monitoring six nursing homes in the state ,","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"including the 268-resident Lambeth House Retirement Community in New Orleans ,","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"where 11 deaths were reported on Tuesday .","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"Numerous hospitals expect to run out of beds within two weeks ,","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"as cases continue to rise .","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"If more beds do n't become available ,","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"`` then we do n't have resources","depth":13},{"id":84,"text":"to save the lives","depth":14},{"id":85,"text":"that we need to save , ''","depth":14},{"id":86,"text":"former Louisiana Secretary of Health Dr. Rebekah Gee said .","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"`` That 's why these stay-at-home orders are so important . ''","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"But `` we have not seen the peak of the crisis yet , ''","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"Gee said .","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"Desperate for protective face masks , Gee said","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"health care workers have been punching holes in plastic office report covers","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"and running string through those holes .","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"`` I think","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"what 's just as concerning is the fact","depth":13},{"id":95,"text":"that we need more ventilators , ''","depth":13},{"id":96,"text":"she said .","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"`` And that is something","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"that the federal government needs to step in","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"and fix . ''","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"Many have called for President Donald Trump to use the Defense Production Act","depth":7},{"id":101,"text":"to speed up the availability of critical health equipment .","depth":7},{"id":102,"text":"This week , Trump and the Federal Emergency Management Agency","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"( FEMA )","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"gave conflicting information","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"about whether the act was being used .","depth":7},{"id":106,"text":"The Grossman School of Medicine is trying to get more doctors into the workforce","depth":6},{"id":107,"text":"to help .","depth":6},{"id":108,"text":"New York will allow two patients to share a single ventilator","depth":5},{"id":109,"text":"In an effort","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"to address the desperate need for medical equipment ,","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"New York state has approved technology","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"that allows two patients to share a ventilator .","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"As of Thursday , more than half of US coronavirus cases were in New York state , with more than 37,000 ,","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"according to CNN 's tally of cases","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"reported by state health officials nationwide .","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"Gov . Andrew Cuomo referred to the method as `` splitting ''","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"and said","depth":11},{"id":118,"text":"it involves adding a second set of tubes to a ventilator .","depth":11},{"id":119,"text":"`` It 's not ideal , ''","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"Cuomo said on Thursday ,","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"`` but we believe","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"it 's workable . ''","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"New York hospitals need about 30,000 ventilators","depth":7},{"id":124,"text":"and have enough personal protection equipment for only the next two weeks ,","depth":8},{"id":125,"text":"the governor has said .","depth":8},{"id":126,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"Cuomo to FEMA :","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"You pick the 26,000 people","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"who are going to die","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":8},{"id":131,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":8},{"id":132,"text":"Cuomo to FEMA :","depth":9},{"id":133,"text":"You pick the 26,000 people","depth":10},{"id":134,"text":"who are going to die","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"00:54","depth":6},{"id":136,"text":"Wednesday , the state had 4,000 ventilators in hospitals and another 4,000 on the way from the federal government .","depth":9},{"id":137,"text":"New York has also purchased 7,000 ventilators","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"and is `` still shopping , ''","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"the governor said .","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"The ventilators are the `` difference between life and death for thousands of New Yorkers , ''","depth":9},{"id":141,"text":"New York City Mayor Bill de Blasio said .","depth":9},{"id":142,"text":"In San Francisco , Mayor London Breed said","depth":9},{"id":143,"text":"her city could see a surge in cases similar to that","depth":10},{"id":144,"text":"seen in New York City .","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"She estimated","depth":10},{"id":146,"text":"San Francisco could need as many as 1,500 more ventilators and 5,000 more hospital beds .","depth":10},{"id":147,"text":"`` If people","depth":14},{"id":148,"text":"who are out on the streets","depth":14},{"id":149,"text":"continue to congregate with one another ,","depth":13},{"id":150,"text":"continue to interact with one another","depth":13},{"id":151,"text":"which increases the spread of this virus ,","depth":13},{"id":152,"text":"we will not have enough beds , enough ICU units , enough ventilators","depth":12},{"id":153,"text":"to support the people","depth":13},{"id":154,"text":"that we know","depth":14},{"id":155,"text":"are going to need them , ''","depth":14},{"id":156,"text":"Breed said .","depth":10},{"id":157,"text":"Across the country , 21 states have issued stay-at-home orders ,","depth":10},{"id":158,"text":"with some not going into effect until the end of the week .","depth":10},{"id":159,"text":"Georgia and Florida do not have statewide rules ,","depth":10},{"id":160,"text":"but Atlanta enacted its own stay-at-home order ,","depth":11},{"id":161,"text":"and Miami announced a nighttime curfew .","depth":11},{"id":162,"text":"In Chicago , Mayor Lori Lightfoot announced Thursday","depth":11},{"id":163,"text":"that bike trails , paths and green spaces will be closed","depth":12},{"id":164,"text":"after crowds were spotted on the city 's lakefront .","depth":12},{"id":165,"text":"`` Congregating on our lakefront ,","depth":14},{"id":166,"text":"to be blunt ,","depth":14},{"id":167,"text":"is going to create a risk","depth":14},{"id":168,"text":"that is unacceptable","depth":15},{"id":169,"text":"and could lead to death , ''","depth":15},{"id":170,"text":"Lightfoot said .","depth":12},{"id":171,"text":"`` Dear God , stay home ,","depth":12},{"id":172,"text":"save lives . ''","depth":12},{"id":173,"text":"The decision comes","depth":11},{"id":174,"text":"after Interim Chicago Police Superintendent Charlie Beck said","depth":12},{"id":175,"text":"police will start issuing citations Thursday to residents","depth":13},{"id":176,"text":"who do not follow rules around social distancing and staying at home .","depth":13},{"id":177,"text":"Breaking the orders is a misdemeanor","depth":13},{"id":178,"text":"punishable by a citation with a fine of up to $ 500 ,","depth":13},{"id":179,"text":"Beck said .","depth":12},{"id":180,"text":"If violation continues ,","depth":12},{"id":181,"text":"it could result in physical arrest .","depth":12},{"id":182,"text":"New York state has restricted nonessential business and gatherings .","depth":10},{"id":183,"text":"Residents are asked to limit outdoor activities to non-contact activities .","depth":10},{"id":184,"text":"Civil fines will be issued to non-compliant businesses , but not to individuals ,","depth":10},{"id":185,"text":"Cuomo said .","depth":10},{"id":186,"text":"In Los Angeles , Mayor Eric Garcetti said","depth":9},{"id":187,"text":"the city also will be enforcing restrictions against non-essential businesses","depth":11},{"id":188,"text":"that are staying open .","depth":11},{"id":189,"text":"But Los Angeles police will not stop people","depth":12},{"id":190,"text":"for exercising and leaving their homes ,","depth":12},{"id":191,"text":"Garcetti said .","depth":11},{"id":192,"text":"The widespread shutdown of businesses","depth":5},{"id":193,"text":"to try to control the outbreak","depth":5},{"id":194,"text":"has led to a record number of Americans","depth":5},{"id":195,"text":"filing for their first week of unemployment benefits .","depth":5},{"id":196,"text":"About 3.3 million Americans filed for initial jobless claims during the week","depth":7},{"id":197,"text":"that ended Saturday ,","depth":7},{"id":198,"text":"according to newly released Department of Labor statistics .","depth":6},{"id":199,"text":"That 's the highest number of initial jobless claims","depth":6},{"id":200,"text":"since the Department of Labor started tracking the data in 1967 .","depth":6},{"id":201,"text":"The previous high was 695,000 claims","depth":6},{"id":202,"text":"filed in the week","depth":7},{"id":203,"text":"ending October 2 , 1982 .","depth":7},{"id":204,"text":"Last week 's jump marked a massive increase from a revised 282,000 claims in the prior week .","depth":5},{"id":205,"text":"Outbreak could last 12 to 18 months","depth":4},{"id":206,"text":"-- if we 're 'lucky '","depth":4},{"id":207,"text":"Hopes","depth":7},{"id":208,"text":"that the outbreak could subside by summer","depth":7},{"id":209,"text":"might not be realistic ,","depth":6},{"id":210,"text":"a Harvard doctor said Thursday .","depth":5},{"id":211,"text":"`` We are going to be living with this , in one form or another , for 12 to 18 months","depth":8},{"id":212,"text":"if we are lucky , ''","depth":8},{"id":213,"text":"said Dr. Ashish Jha , director of the Harvard Global Health Institute .","depth":7},{"id":214,"text":"That time frame refers to how long","depth":9},{"id":215,"text":"health officials predict","depth":9},{"id":216,"text":"it will take","depth":9},{"id":217,"text":"to make a publicly available vaccine","depth":9},{"id":218,"text":"`` Once we have a vaccine","depth":10},{"id":219,"text":"that 's effective and widely deployed ,","depth":10},{"id":220,"text":"we can bring the pandemic to an end , ''","depth":9},{"id":221,"text":"Jha said .","depth":8},{"id":222,"text":"`` Until that time , we are going to continue to have to confront and deal with the virus . ''","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":445,"left":414,"right":444,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":414,"left":279,"right":413,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":279,"left":241,"right":278,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":241,"left":0,"right":240,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":240,"left":234,"right":239,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":234,"left":231,"right":233,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":231,"left":229,"right":230,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":229,"left":227,"right":228,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":227,"left":225,"right":226,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":225,"left":1,"right":224,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":224,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":226,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":228,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":230,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":233,"left":10,"right":232,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":232,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":239,"left":237,"right":238,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":237,"left":13,"right":236,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":236,"left":14,"right":235,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":235,"left":15,"right":16,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":238,"left":17,"right":18,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":278,"left":248,"right":277,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":248,"left":19,"right":247,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":247,"left":244,"right":246,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":244,"left":242,"right":243,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":242,"left":20,"right":21,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{